Feature: Fix Broken Pipeline & Wire Google Cloud Vision OCR

  System Architecture

  Components That Must Exist

  1. Database layer (Better-SQLite3) — source of truth for items
  2. File upload API — validates and stores images
  3. Scheduler/worker — polls queue, dispatches jobs
  4. Image resizing — generates thumbnails + web-optimized versions (Sharp)
  5. OCR service — extracts text from images (Google Cloud Vision)
  6. AI enrichment pipeline — Conductor (categorize) + Experts (extract reseller data)
  7. State machine — manages item through processing stages

  Component Dependencies

  Upload API → Database ✓ (working)
              → Scheduler (broken, needs activation)
                          → Image Resizing (incomplete)
                          → OCR Worker (basic, needs Cloud Vision)
                          → AI Enrichment (weak, needs expert prompts)

  Data Flow

  User uploads image
    ↓ Validates + stores in DB
    ↓ Scheduler picks up job
    ↓ Resize image (thumbnail + web version)
    ↓ OCR text from image (Cloud Vision)
    ↓ AI categorizes (Conductor prompt) → picks expert
    ↓ Expert analyzes (domain-specific extraction)
    ↓ Stores results in DB (title, value indicators, keywords, condition, analysis_history)
    ↓ UI displays enriched item

